I originally had the same error as MisayaZ, but it went away when I removed an old Protobuf package that I had installed with yum (I installed TensorFlow and its Protobuf dependency with Pip).

Now I'm getting a different error when I try to compile the ZeroOut Op from the "Adding a New Op" tutorial. This is my error:

In file included from /home/jpaparia/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/include/tensorflow/core/framework/op.h:22:0,
                 from zero_out.cc:1:
/home/jpaparia/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/include/tensorflow/core/
framework/op_def.pb.h:9:42: fatal error: google/protobuf/stubs/common.h: No such file or directory
 #include <google/protobuf/stubs/common.h>
                                          ^
compilation terminated.

Any idea what might cause this error? Thanks!
